Authors:
Viviane Oliveira Garcia, M Fronza, R Von Borowski,
Genivaldo Alves-Silva, A.R. Zimmer, T Ruaro, Simone C.B. Gnoatto, A
Dallegrave, Rosa Mara Borges da Silveira
Title:
First Report on Chemical Composition and Cytotoxicy
Evaluation of Foraminispora rugosa basidiomata
Abstract:
Foraminispora rugosa was described from Atlantic Forest
specimens and it is a basidiomycete in Ganodermataceae family. In this
study, chemical composition and cytotoxicity of F. rugosa ethanolic
extract were investigated for the first time. Five oxylipins were
identified by Ultra Hight Performance Liquid Chromatography coupled to
Quadrupole Time-of-Flight and Mass Spectrometry (UHPLC-QTOF-MS). The
ethanolic extract was weakly toxic to the tested cell lines, suggesting
that it can be tested for biological activities with relative
selectivity and safety.
